      • ClickTab

        public static boolean ClickTab(Component tabcontrol,
               java.lang.String value)
        Select a tab value in Tab Control and verify the value has been selected.

        See Detailed Reference

        Parameters:
        tabcontrol - Component (from App Map) to select a tab from.
        value - String, text value
        Returns:
        true if successful, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        SeleniumPlus.prevResults, TestRecordData.getStatusCode(), TestRecordData.getStatusInfo()
        Example:
         boolean success = TabControl.ClickTab(Map.SAPDemo.TabStrip,"Mort.Calc");

      • ClickTabContains

        public static boolean ClickTabContains(Component tabcontrol,
                       java.lang.String value)
        Select a tab value in Tab Control, the value will be matched partially.

        See Detailed Reference

        Parameters:
        tabcontrol - Component (from App Map) to select a tab from.
        value - String, partial text value to match
        Returns:
        true if successful, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        SeleniumPlus.prevResults, TestRecordData.getStatusCode(), TestRecordData.getStatusInfo()
        Example:
         boolean success = TabControl.ClickTabContains(Map.SAPDemo.TabStrip,"Calc");//For tab 'Mort.Calc'

      • SelectTabIndex

        public static boolean SelectTabIndex(Component tabcontrol,
                     int index)
        Select a tab by index in Tab Control and verify the index has been selected.

        See Detailed Reference

        Parameters:
        tabcontrol - Component (from App Map) to select a tab from.
        index - int, the index to select, it is 1-based.
        Returns:
        true if successful, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        SeleniumPlus.prevResults, TestRecordData.getStatusCode(), TestRecordData.getStatusInfo()
        Example:
         boolean success = TabControl.SelectTabIndex(Map.SAPDemo.TabStrip,1);//Select the first tab
